      "content": "While maintaining good hydration with increased water intake is crucial, simply doubling your water consumption to try to flush lithium from your system isn't guaranteed to work and can actually increase the risk of lithium toxicity. Your body does not typically excrete lithium at an increased rate by merely drinking more water. It would be better to continue to monitor your symptoms and follow your healthcare provider's guidance on how to manage them. If adjusting lithium levels is necessary, it should be done professionally. Remember to consult your doctor rather than taking actions based on online advice.",
